A '''Computationally enhanced craft item''' (CETI) is a simple [[mechanical device]] that is fitted with a small computer or [[computer interface]] and a [[Servomechanism|servo system]]. A larger computer programs or directly controls the CETI according to the wishes of the user-programmer. CETIs are educational devices, but they can possibly provide guidance towards a future of user-programmable robots and [[ubiquitous computing]]. Tom Wrensch was one of the earliest proponents of CETI.

