A '''course reader''' is a [[publication]] type used for teaching in universities and [[academia]].{{citation needed|date=February 2014}} A course reader is made up of a collection of existing texts, course slides and notes etc. Common forms of course readers include; photocopy packs or [[PDF documents]]. Course readers require [[copyright]] clearance.<ref>http://copytech.mit.edu/course-readers-copyright-clearance</ref>

